**Segments**

- **Product Type**: The immunoassay reagents and devices market can be segmented based on product type into reagents & kits, analyzers, and software & services. Reagents & kits segment is further classified into antibodies, antigens, enzymes, and others. Analyzers include chemiluminescence immunoassay (CLIA) analyzers, enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) analyzers, and others.

- **Technology**: Under the technology segment, the market can be categorized into radioimmunoassay (RIA), enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA), fluorescence immunoassay (FIA), chemiluminescence immunoassay (CLIA), and others. Each technology has its specific applications and advantages, catering to different needs within the healthcare industry.

- **Application**: The immunoassay reagents and devices market can also be segmented based on application, including infectious diseases, endocrinology, oncology, autoimmune disorders, cardiology, and others. These applications reflect the diverse range of diseases and conditions that immunoassay tests can help diagnose and monitor.

**Market Players**

- **Key Players**: Prominent players in the immunoassay reagents and devices market include F. Hoffmann-La Roche Ltd, Siemens Healthineers, Abbott, Danaher, bioMérieux SA, Thermo Fisher Scientific Inc., Ortho Clinical Diagnostics, QIAGEN, BD, Agilent Technologies, Inc., Sysmex Corporation, DiaSorin S.p.A, Merck KGaA, and PerkinElmer Inc. These companies are at the forefront of developing innovative immunoassay products and technologies to meet the growing demand for accurate diagnostic solutions.

